4 Species niche

library(grassland)
theme_set(ggthemes::theme_few())

Download biogeography (occurrence) data from four sources: BIEN, CCH, GBIF, iNat.

spp_tbl <- tidy_taxonomy_consolidate(dat_community = dat_community)
path_occ <- down_biogeography(species_table = spp_tbl) # needs parallel computation
dat_occ_full <- read_biogeography(path_occ = path_occ, gbif_only = F)
dat_occ <- read_biogeography(path_occ = path_occ, gbif_only = T)
dat_occ_full <- read_biogeography(gbif_only = F)
gg_biogeography <- plot_biogeography(dat_occ_full)
gg_biogeography

df_summ_occ <- summ_biogeography(dat_occ = dat_occ_full)
df_summ_occ
#>   source  n_occ n_sp
#> 1   gbif 830870  374
#> 2   bien 102352  251
#> 3    cch 230903  377
#> 4   inat 552033  350

We retrieved 830870 occurrence records of 374 species in the CFP from the Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF).

Calculate and summarize species climate niches.

dat_clim <- read_climate()
path_trait <- calc_individual_trait(dat_occ, dat_clim, occ_source = "gbif", clim_source = "chelsa")
dat_trait <- read_individual_trait(path_trait = path_trait)
dat_niche <- calc_species_niche(dat_trait, add_dummy = T)
df_summ_niche <- summ_species_niche(dat_niche = dat_niche)

Among all the 377 species with more than 100 GBIF records, their average temperatures ranging from 8.15 C to 17.5 C, and their average precipitations ranging from 229 mm to 1,410 mm.

Danthonia californica had 991 records, with temperature of 12.5 (5.5 -15.3 )C and precipitation of 1,110 (510-2,750) mm, whereas Stipa pulchra had 1749 records, with temperature of 15.3 (12.9 -17.4 )C and precipitation of 549 (279-1,110) mm.

gg_niche$sp_niche

Calculate all species climate niches temperature and precipitation correlation.

mod_species_niche_cor <- test_species_niche(dat_niche = dat_niche)
mod_species_niche_cor
#> 
#>  Pearson's product-moment correlation
#> 
#> data:  dat_niche$tmp_occ_median and dat_niche$ppt_occ_median
#> t = -16.004, df = 375, p-value < 2.2e-16
#> alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
#> 95 percent confidence interval:
#>  -0.6934349 -0.5729123
#> sample estimates:
#>       cor 
#> -0.637051

Across all the species, the temperature and precipitation averages were negatively and significantly correlated (Pearsons correlation r = -0.637051).
